name: 04-Model Training and Evaluation
content:
Model Training and Evaluation

Model Used:

  • H2O Distributed Random Forest (DRF)
  • Chosen due to scalability, robustness with mixed feature types, and strong performance in fraud classification tasks.

Features Details (sample):

  • Transaction Attributes: Amount, Transaction Reason, Transaction Frequency.
  • Demographics: Gender, Job, City Population.
  • Location: State.
  • Historical Labels: Fraud_Label (supervised training).

Feature Importance:

The DRF model provides variable importance based on impurity reduction and predictive power.

Likely top features:

  • Transaction Amount (higher = more suspicious).
  • Transaction Frequency (unusual spikes indicate risk).
  • Job & State (sectoral & regional fraud hotspots).

Model Metrics:

  • Accuracy – Overall prediction correctness.
  • Precision – Focused on correctly flagged frauds.
  • Recall (Sensitivity) – Ability to capture actual frauds.
  • F1 Score – Balanced measure for fraud detection.
  • ROC-AUC – Probability discrimination ability.
